  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f11b9afa3c1cc781ca0ff087a29d87",
        "content": [
          "Key Specifications: \r\n",
          "- RealCID and CID are the same - it doesn't matter what you are using to show results \r\n",
          "- Never order by CID/RealCID/PositionID or any ID unless asked specifically \r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "1. Data Scope & Join Rules\r\n",
          "Current Status: ALWAYS filter customer_snapshot_v by Yesterday(DateID).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Historical Data: ALWAYS use customer_snapshot_v with specific DateID filters (do not use the MAX filter).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Base Join Logic: Link all views by the CID concept. Use RealCID when joining customer_snapshot_v, cfd_statusinfo_v, bi_output_vg_mimo_slim, bi_output_vg_aum_slim and bi_output_vg_revenue_slim.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Action vs. Validation Dates: When asked about actions (trades/deposits) in \"Period A\" by users who were valid in \"Period B\":\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Filter the action table by its DateID (or OpenDateID) for Period A.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Join with customer_snapshot_v on RealCID.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Filter customer_snapshot_v by DateID for Period B.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Ambiguous Timeframes: If a user asks for activity but does not specify a validation date, you MUST ask: \"Should I validate the users' status based on the date the activity occurred, or based on their status on a specific snapshot date (e.g., today)?\"\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "2. Filtering & Trend Rules\r\n",
          "Trend Reporting (De-duplication): To avoid double-counting users in periodic trends, apply the following exact filters to customer_snapshot_v:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Weekly: IsLastDayWeek = 1\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Monthly: IsLastDayMonth = 1\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Quarterly: IsLastDayQuarter = 1\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Yearly: IsLastDayYear = 1\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Verified Users: Filter by VerificationLevel = 3.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Active KYC Profiles: Always filter kyc_for_compliance_v by Is_Current = 1 unless history is specifically requested.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "3. Common SQL Expressions (CSE) & Business Logic\r\n",
          "Club Members: When filtering for club members, strictly use the predefined IsClub CSE (customer_snapshot_v.PlayerLevelID in (2,5,6,7,3)).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Blocked Users: When identifying blocked users, apply the predefined IsBlocked CSE.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Profit & Loss (P&L): Use the relevant predefined P&L CSEs for total financial impact instead of calculating manually.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Net Deposit: Calculate as GlobalDepositsAmount - GlobalWithdrawsAmount.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "First Time Depositor (FTD): Identify FTDs using TotalFTDGlobalCount = 1.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Revenue Aggregation: Always use SUM(RevenueAmount). For \"Total Revenue\" or \"Net Revenue,\" apply the filter IncludedInTotalRevenue = 1.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Active Traders: Count unique RealCID in the revenue view where CountAsActiveTrade = 1.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "4. Formatting & Guardrails\r\n",
          "Presence Equals Validity: If a record exists for a user in customer_snapshot_v for a specific DateID, that user is strictly considered valid for that date.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Date Formats: Use YYYYMMDD (Integer) for all ID-based filtering. Use YYYY-MM-DD for display outputs.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Currency: Format P&L, Revenue, and MIMO amounts as Currency ($).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "5. Contextual Awareness\r\n",
          "Session Continuity: ALWAYS review the current session's chat history before generating a response. Maintain consistency with previously defined logic, view definitions, and user preferences established during this conversation."
        ]
      }
